This paper is about learning representations for counterfactual inference using neural networks. The most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on training neural networks for this task. Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CE (Computational Engineering), cs.CY (Cryptography and Security), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as these areas are relevant to the development and application of counterfactual inference methods.
